02:36.641 --> 02:39.009
[ Inhales ]

02:43.715 --> 02:46.117
[ Exhales ]

02:47.719 --> 02:53.357
Mmm.

02:53.359 --> 02:56.026
Hey.

02:56.028 --> 02:58.149
I know you.

03:03.136 --> 03:05.303
Now, where you headed?

03:05.305 --> 03:08.873
Daniel: I don't know.

03:08.875 --> 03:13.678
Not all who wander are lost.

03:13.680 --> 03:17.682
Yeah.

03:17.684 --> 03:19.651
Till you get things figured out,
you reckon you could give me

03:19.653 --> 03:22.520
a hand with a little chore?

03:22.522 --> 03:24.656
I don't mind.

03:24.658 --> 03:25.790
[ Inhales ]

03:25.792 --> 03:27.892
"Can do" attitude.

03:30.729 --> 03:34.892
[ Music ]

03:51.218 --> 03:53.586
How'd you get here?

03:53.588 --> 03:55.321
Kerwin: Through the wall.

03:59.560 --> 04:01.561
That's not possible.

04:02.830 --> 04:04.231
Shh.

04:04.233 --> 04:06.767
It's weird, isn't it?

04:08.269 --> 04:09.670
What is?

04:09.672 --> 04:13.007
That I know exactly
when I'm gonna die.

04:14.676 --> 04:18.046
That's very sad, Kerwin.

04:18.048 --> 04:21.550
It has its pluses.

04:21.552 --> 04:23.719
You can grieve your own death.

04:27.291 --> 04:31.693
[ Music ]

04:39.138 --> 04:44.808
[ Laughter ]

04:57.858 --> 05:00.059
[ Car door slams ]

05:21.648 --> 05:23.348
Forgot my key.

05:36.728 --> 05:41.968
Shh... [ Bleating ]

06:05.858 --> 06:09.393
Hey, can I stay
back here with 'em?

06:09.395 --> 06:11.395
Nah, they'll be fine.

06:11.397 --> 06:13.197
I'm the one need the company.

06:14.933 --> 06:19.312
[ Music ]

06:21.708 --> 06:24.409
Slide down.

06:24.411 --> 06:26.678
Get low in your seat.

06:26.680 --> 06:29.114
Best they don't see
that you're with me.

06:32.752 --> 06:34.987
You can peek out
once in a while.

06:39.193 --> 06:42.798
[ Music ]

06:49.137 --> 06:50.136
Oh!

06:50.138 --> 06:52.003
Damn!

06:56.510 --> 07:00.445
[ Music ]

07:00.447 --> 07:04.850
[ Bleating ]

07:07.720 --> 07:14.860
[ Baby crying ]

07:17.230 --> 07:20.532
[ Chatter, sirens wailing ]

07:26.740 --> 07:28.441
Ah!

07:43.424 --> 07:45.765
Where'd ya go, son?

07:50.398 --> 07:52.899
You wanna see
somethin' different?

07:57.705 --> 08:00.139
Know you're tempted,
but don't peek.

08:00.141 --> 08:04.176
[ Cattle mooing ]

08:08.449 --> 08:10.350
There she blows.

08:13.020 --> 08:16.933
[ Music ]

08:19.227 --> 08:21.695
Somebody made that up.

08:25.198 --> 08:29.067
[ Music ]

08:29.069 --> 08:32.736
It's the beauty that hurts
you most, son, not the ugly.

08:35.274 --> 08:40.283
[ Music ]

09:19.648 --> 09:24.119
[ Grunting ]

09:29.926 --> 09:32.194
Ha-ha-ha!

09:32.196 --> 09:35.397
[ Grunting ]

09:38.602 --> 09:39.935
Ow!

09:39.937 --> 09:40.769
Ha!

09:40.771 --> 09:41.737
Huh.

09:41.739 --> 09:43.272
Ha-ha.

09:46.377 --> 09:51.648
[ Grunting ]

09:57.154 --> 09:58.187
You ain't goin' nowhere.

09:58.189 --> 09:58.988
Come here.

09:58.990 --> 10:00.189
Come here, you.

10:00.191 --> 10:01.924
Come on.

10:03.294 --> 10:07.763
[ Panting ]

10:07.765 --> 10:10.866
[ Music ]

10:10.868 --> 10:13.069
Come on.

10:13.071 --> 10:18.475
[ Panting ]

10:22.513 --> 10:25.782
He's skinny, but he's furkid.

10:25.784 --> 10:27.284
Ha.

10:27.286 --> 10:32.243
[ Music ]

10:51.509 --> 10:54.345
[ Goats bleating ]

11:13.532 --> 11:17.235
This is your trip, but
you're about to pull a 360.

11:17.237 --> 11:20.305
You gonna run 'em off a cliff?

11:20.307 --> 11:21.473
What?

11:21.475 --> 11:22.640
Like swine?

11:25.711 --> 11:27.611
You read too much.

11:32.818 --> 11:34.485
I put a knot on your head.

11:34.487 --> 11:36.854
I think so.

11:36.856 --> 11:40.024
[ Laughter ]

11:43.729 --> 11:45.029
[ Snorts ]

11:45.031 --> 11:45.997
Oh.

11:45.999 --> 11:47.865
[ Snorting ]

11:47.867 --> 11:50.534
Oh!

11:50.536 --> 11:52.770
Once it opens up,
it's hard to staunch.

11:55.307 --> 11:56.575
Whoa, Nelly.

11:56.577 --> 11:58.677
What?

11:58.679 --> 12:00.312
Stop.

12:00.314 --> 12:01.146
What?

12:01.148 --> 12:03.014
Stop!

12:10.856 --> 12:13.157
That's it?

12:13.159 --> 12:15.526
That's the sign you
was lookin' for?

12:15.528 --> 12:17.929
Them damn things is everywhere.

12:20.432 --> 12:21.866
Hey!

12:21.868 --> 12:23.435
You did me a solid.

12:23.437 --> 12:27.739
It's yours.

12:27.741 --> 12:28.941
I don't want any.

12:28.943 --> 12:31.410
You can't get nowhere in
this world without money.

12:33.814 --> 12:36.362
[ Music ]

12:42.556 --> 12:46.026
Hey.

12:46.028 --> 12:47.727
Are you real?

12:47.729 --> 12:49.630
Am I real?

12:50.565 --> 12:53.700
[ Laughter ]

12:53.702 --> 12:55.869
I want some of what
you're takin'.

12:55.871 --> 12:59.206
[ Laughter ]

13:01.109 --> 13:05.926
[ Music ]

13:19.795 --> 13:21.863
[ Beeping ]

13:22.865 --> 13:24.833
Tawney: Welcome home, husband.

13:24.835 --> 13:25.767
Ted: Hi.

13:25.769 --> 13:27.001
How was it?

13:27.003 --> 13:27.835
Informative.

13:27.837 --> 13:28.736
In a good way?

13:28.738 --> 13:31.806
Maybe.

13:31.808 --> 13:33.841
Hey.

13:33.843 --> 13:35.309
Hey.

13:35.311 --> 13:39.680
I missed you.

13:39.682 --> 13:40.715
Teddy?

13:40.717 --> 13:42.283
Yeah.

13:42.285 --> 13:44.452
I want you to keep an open mind.

13:44.454 --> 13:46.921
Okay.

13:46.923 --> 13:52.260
I believe there's been a
miracle, a real miracle.

13:52.262 --> 13:53.628
Really?

13:53.630 --> 13:56.431
It was the most
beautiful thing, Teddy.

13:56.433 --> 13:59.501
It strengthened my faith.

13:59.503 --> 14:02.403
What happened?

14:02.405 --> 14:06.841
Daniel's gonna be saved.

14:06.843 --> 14:08.376
What?

14:17.552 --> 14:23.065
[ Music ]

14:39.876 --> 14:43.632
Ted: Daniel, what
a nice surprise.

14:46.783 --> 14:49.183
Is everything okay?

14:49.185 --> 14:52.520
Remember when you were a kid,
and you came back to that

14:52.522 --> 14:59.261
place you were years later,
and everything seemed so small?

14:59.263 --> 15:00.696
Yeah.

15:00.698 --> 15:04.466
But, it seems bigger now.

15:04.468 --> 15:06.768
You want some coffee?

15:06.770 --> 15:10.473
It's nothin' fancy, just made.

15:10.475 --> 15:12.208
I'd like that, Ted.

15:18.427 --> 15:20.695
Tawney: Well, we were getting
ready for the jubilee.

15:20.697 --> 15:22.096
Ted Jr.: At our church?

15:22.098 --> 15:23.764
Uh, yes.

15:23.766 --> 15:27.535
And we were making casseroles,
and-and-- oh, Pastor Beau

15:27.537 --> 15:29.538
met him and was so welcoming.

15:29.540 --> 15:31.173
And we got to talkin'.

15:31.175 --> 15:33.508
You and-- you and
Daniel got to talkin'?

15:33.510 --> 15:37.079
Yes, Teddy, about big things.

15:37.081 --> 15:40.449
S-so, you invited
him to our church?

15:40.451 --> 15:43.753
Isn't that what we're
supposed to do as Christians?

15:43.755 --> 15:45.321
Well, of course, it is, Tawney.

15:45.323 --> 15:47.790
But, I mean, our church?

15:47.792 --> 15:51.528
Honey, they're practically the last
group that buys tires from us.

15:51.530 --> 15:54.130
Well, that's not gonna stop.

15:54.132 --> 15:55.499
[ Sighs ]

15:55.501 --> 15:57.334
What?

15:57.336 --> 16:00.404
It just doesn't make
any sense to me.

16:00.406 --> 16:02.406
What doesn't?

16:02.408 --> 16:05.009
I mean, look, the Holdens have
never been religious people.

16:05.011 --> 16:06.244
I mean, none of 'em.

16:06.246 --> 16:08.146
And I'm pretty sure Amantha's
a full-blown atheist,

16:08.148 --> 16:11.216
and if she does believe in God,
she probably hates his guts.

16:11.218 --> 16:14.786
Why can't you ever see
the good in people?

16:14.788 --> 16:15.953
I see good in people.

16:15.955 --> 16:19.757
And why can't God perform
miracles in this town, right now?

16:19.759 --> 16:20.791
Of course, he can.

16:20.793 --> 16:24.028
- I-I--
- I saw it in his eyes.

16:24.030 --> 16:25.796
You saw what?

16:25.798 --> 16:29.099
A goodness and a need.

16:29.101 --> 16:30.934
A need for what?

16:30.936 --> 16:35.371
For God, Teddy, a need for God.

16:35.373 --> 16:36.406
Oh, boy.

16:36.408 --> 16:41.777
He wants to be cleansed--
cleansed of all he's been through.

16:41.779 --> 16:45.514
Now, I saw it, and I felt it.

16:45.516 --> 16:52.321
He's-he's seekin'--
what's that word?

16:52.323 --> 16:54.890
He's seekin' absolution.

16:54.892 --> 16:57.325
Why do you care
about him so much?

16:57.327 --> 17:00.895
Because he's one of God's
children, and-and I believe

17:00.897 --> 17:07.134
he has suffered unjustly,
terribly so, maybe more than Job.

17:07.136 --> 17:08.869
[ Sighs ]

17:08.872 --> 17:10.371
What?

17:10.373 --> 17:13.775
Nothin'.

17:13.777 --> 17:16.944
Why do you hate him so much?

17:16.945 --> 17:18.179
Hate him?

17:18.181 --> 17:19.780
I don't even know him.

17:19.781 --> 17:21.816
Hell, that's part
of the problem.

17:21.818 --> 17:23.818
All I know, is he got off
death row six days ago

17:23.819 --> 17:26.487
on some DNA thing I still
don't fully understand.

17:26.489 --> 17:29.790
And now, you're hangin' out with
him, as soon as I leave town!

17:39.400 --> 17:41.501
Daniel: It was nice of
you to marry my mother.

17:41.503 --> 17:44.204
Ted: Nice of me?

17:44.206 --> 17:45.906
I'm the lucky one.

17:49.810 --> 17:51.777
I remember him.

17:56.016 --> 17:57.650
I'm not plannin' to work here.

17:57.652 --> 18:01.721
I just wanted you to know.

18:01.723 --> 18:04.423
Somebody been talkin' to you?

18:04.425 --> 18:09.929
When I was a kid, I-- even then,
I knew I wouldn't work here.

18:09.931 --> 18:13.233
I just wasn't...

18:18.272 --> 18:21.442
I wanted to tell
him, but I couldn't.

18:21.444 --> 18:26.714
Somethin' like that would be hard
for a boy to tell his father.

18:26.716 --> 18:29.383
In hindsight, I'm glad I didn't.

18:45.666 --> 18:51.471
You don't trust my
judgment, do you?

18:51.473 --> 18:55.242
I think you see the good in
everybody you meet, Tawney.

18:55.244 --> 18:59.113
But, I'm here to tell you
not all people are good.

18:59.115 --> 19:03.618
I know good, decent people,
people I've known my whole life,

19:03.620 --> 19:05.987
people I would trust
my own children with,

19:05.989 --> 19:10.625
that believe in their hearts that
he is a cold-blooded killer.

19:10.627 --> 19:14.763
And you can't dismiss that just
because you don't want it to be true.

19:14.765 --> 19:17.132
Now, look, I'll give him
the benefit of the doubt.

19:17.134 --> 19:17.866
Okay?

19:17.868 --> 19:24.506
For you, for mom, for dad,
Jared, hell, even Amantha.

19:24.508 --> 19:29.378
All I'm saying, is for him to be
on death row all those years,

19:29.380 --> 19:32.181
knowing what was facing him,
and he didn't do nothin'

19:32.183 --> 19:36.051
to get right with the Lord, and
then he gets out, and in six days,

19:36.053 --> 19:37.986
he gets testified to by
some pretty, young woman--

19:37.988 --> 19:39.621
- I don't appreciate--
- ...and all of a sudden,

19:39.623 --> 19:43.025
he's filled with the spirit!

19:43.027 --> 19:49.732
I'm sorry, but that seems
pretty damn suspicious to me.

19:49.734 --> 19:56.806
I don't think--
I believe he meant it.

20:00.010 --> 20:02.645
Then there's nothin'
left to talk about.

20:09.218 --> 20:11.553
I'm gonna go check on dad.

20:11.555 --> 20:16.658
Got the big semi-annual
tire sale comin' up.

20:16.660 --> 20:18.493
A lot of good that's gonna do.

20:24.466 --> 20:25.400
[ Country music plays ]

20:25.402 --> 20:35.344
♪ There's nothing to do on a lonely
Friday night except drive into town ♪

20:35.346 --> 20:40.950
♪ and turn around at the church
of Christ and wave to your ♪

20:40.952 --> 20:44.186
♪ friends as they go passing by ♪

20:49.125 --> 20:51.126
Hey, bud.

20:51.128 --> 20:52.227
See the dancing man?

20:52.229 --> 20:55.531
Hope you got it on sale.

20:55.533 --> 20:59.269
Got all the fliers, 5,000.

20:59.271 --> 21:01.438
Five thousand?

21:01.440 --> 21:02.105
Got a good deal.

21:02.107 --> 21:03.273
Don't worry.

21:03.275 --> 21:06.677
I'm worried where we're gonna
find 5,000 cars to put 'em on.

21:06.679 --> 21:09.780
One at a time.

21:09.782 --> 21:11.348
I think we'll be lucky to
get one in five hundred

21:11.350 --> 21:12.916
of those to even come in.

21:12.918 --> 21:14.952
That'll be somethin'.

21:14.954 --> 21:17.821
- How was the seminar?
- It was okay.

21:17.823 --> 21:19.991
Everything all right at home?

21:19.993 --> 21:20.591
Yeah-- it's fine, dad.

21:20.593 --> 21:22.693
Where-where's the
ceramic mechanic?

21:22.695 --> 21:23.661
Oh, Daniel took it.

21:23.663 --> 21:25.663
What?

21:25.665 --> 21:27.131
Well, he came by here.

21:27.133 --> 21:28.832
He looked kinda pitiful, too.

21:28.834 --> 21:30.200
Yeah.
He's got that look down.

21:30.202 --> 21:31.668
What did he want
with the mechanic?

21:31.670 --> 21:34.104
- Well, it belonged to his daddy.
- It belongs to the store!

21:34.106 --> 21:35.772
Well, I didn't know you
cared so much for it.

21:35.774 --> 21:37.440
I touch it every day
that I come in here!

21:37.442 --> 21:38.408
Really?

21:38.410 --> 21:40.977
Why?

21:40.979 --> 21:43.446
I don't know, luck or--
never mind why I touch it.

21:43.448 --> 21:45.748
The point is, I touch it!

21:45.750 --> 21:47.918
We'll get another one.

21:47.920 --> 21:50.520
[ Sighs ]

21:50.522 --> 21:52.756
That's not the point, dad.

21:59.998 --> 22:03.902
Why don't you go back
home, get some rest,

22:03.904 --> 22:06.771
and I'll put out the fliers?

22:06.773 --> 22:08.840
No, I'll put 'em out.

22:08.842 --> 22:10.731
I need to get some fresh air.

22:15.149 --> 22:17.115
Ugh...

22:20.320 --> 22:26.114
[ Music ]

22:57.859 --> 23:00.260
Amantha: Do we know what
time he made his escape?

23:00.262 --> 23:04.298
Janet: No, but he stopped by the
store mid-morning to see your dad.

23:04.300 --> 23:05.299
Dad?

23:05.301 --> 23:08.335
Oh, Ted, I mean.

23:08.337 --> 23:10.371
Ted say how he was doin'?

23:10.373 --> 23:12.273
Disheveled.

23:12.275 --> 23:13.507
So, what do we do?

23:13.509 --> 23:16.110
Call the men in white coats?

23:16.112 --> 23:18.512
Are there still men
in white coats?

23:18.514 --> 23:19.446
I hope not.

23:19.448 --> 23:22.750
Hmm... how about the
men in white hats?

23:22.752 --> 23:25.586
They never existed.

23:25.588 --> 23:28.222
Deep down, you're darker
than I am, mother.

23:28.224 --> 23:29.623
Admit it.

23:29.625 --> 23:34.528
I don't think I wanna
do that, Amantha.

23:34.530 --> 23:39.500
Well, I guess we
just wait, then.

23:39.502 --> 23:40.568
I think so.

23:40.570 --> 23:44.572
- He'll be--
- Fucked up.

23:44.574 --> 23:47.274
I'm gonna start finishing
my own sentences.

23:47.276 --> 23:52.546
Please, mother, don't take
away one of my few pleasures.

23:52.548 --> 23:53.813
Mom!

23:53.815 --> 23:54.781
Janet!

23:54.783 --> 23:57.050
It's Teddy!

23:57.052 --> 23:59.820
Lord works in mysterious ways.

23:59.822 --> 24:03.623
Be right down!

24:03.625 --> 24:06.660
I hope it's okay I just dropped
by like I always have.

24:06.662 --> 24:08.295
Of course.

24:08.297 --> 24:09.095
No pie.

24:09.097 --> 24:10.797
That's okay.
No worries.

24:10.799 --> 24:13.366
There's monkey bread
on the counter.

24:13.368 --> 24:14.701
Teddy?

24:14.703 --> 24:20.040
Sure.

24:20.042 --> 24:22.742
So, Daniel adjusting okay?

24:22.744 --> 24:24.544
Splendidly.

24:24.546 --> 24:27.247
I can't say I wasn't a little
surprised by his decision.

24:27.249 --> 24:28.915
Decision?

24:28.917 --> 24:30.150
He didn't tell ya?

24:30.152 --> 24:31.618
What decision?

24:31.620 --> 24:33.453
Turning his life
over to the Lord.

24:33.455 --> 24:35.789
What?

24:35.791 --> 24:37.491
Washed in the blood.

24:37.493 --> 24:39.793
What in the hell are you
talkin' about, Teddy?

24:39.795 --> 24:42.664
Daniel's getting baptized
tonight at the jubilee.

24:45.601 --> 24:47.568
I assumed ya'll knew.

24:50.034 --> 24:56.239
[ Music ]

24:58.042 --> 25:03.614
[ Chatter, laughter ]

25:16.227 --> 25:18.228
Jared: Hey, Daniel.

25:18.230 --> 25:23.666
Daniel: Hey, Jared.

25:23.668 --> 25:25.234
Been a while.

25:25.236 --> 25:29.205
Yeah-- heard that.

25:29.207 --> 25:33.209
It's a trip thinkin' of
you being here, now.

25:33.211 --> 25:35.979
Yeah, I bet.

25:35.981 --> 25:38.649
Can we help you with something?

25:47.627 --> 25:50.028
Uh, you want me to call mom?

25:50.030 --> 25:53.699
See if she can come pick you up?

25:53.701 --> 25:56.001
I'll walk.

25:56.003 --> 25:58.070
Thank you, though.

26:03.376 --> 26:05.277
Get back to class.

26:06.813 --> 26:08.881
Ted Jr.: Daniel and Tawney
been hanging out a little bit.

26:08.883 --> 26:10.049
Amantha: When?

26:10.051 --> 26:11.917
When I was out of town, for one.

26:11.919 --> 26:13.219
They met at the church.

26:13.221 --> 26:14.620
She might've hung out with
him here-- I don't know.

26:14.622 --> 26:15.488
She hasn't.

26:15.490 --> 26:16.155
How do you know?

26:16.157 --> 26:17.022
What's your point?

26:17.024 --> 26:17.857
My point?

26:17.859 --> 26:18.991
Mmm-hmm.

26:18.993 --> 26:21.260
You ever think how it makes me
feel to have to come over here?

26:21.262 --> 26:22.995
I don't really care
how you feel, Ted.

26:22.997 --> 26:25.831
Janet: Amantha.

26:25.833 --> 26:27.967
I just thought you'd like to know.
That's all.

26:27.969 --> 26:29.402
Thought you assumed
we already did.

26:29.404 --> 26:32.371
In case you didn't.

26:32.373 --> 26:36.009
Boy, I knew you'd crucify the
messenger, especially if it was me.

26:36.011 --> 26:38.245
Oh, I'm sure it was just torture
for you to come over here

26:38.247 --> 26:40.147
and drop a big, fat
turd right at our feet.

26:40.149 --> 26:41.581
- That's enough.
- Bless your little heart.

26:41.583 --> 26:43.550
Really!

26:45.653 --> 26:47.487
[ Door closing ]

26:47.489 --> 26:49.356
Hello?

26:49.358 --> 26:51.158
Danny?

26:54.863 --> 26:58.466
Well, great monkey bread.

